      "updated": 1772584706678,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The Docker Engine is the core \nopen-source containerization \ntechnology used to build, run, and \nmanage containerized applications. \nIt serves as a client-server application \nthat virtualizes the host operating \nsystem to provide isolated environments \nfor software to run consistently \nacross different platforms. ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The Docker Engine is the core \nopen-source containerization \ntechnology used to build, run, and \nmanage containerized applications. \nIt serves as a client-server application \nthat virtualizes the host operating \nsystem to provide isolated environments \nfor software to run consistently \nacross different platforms. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
